            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH SERVICES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ASSISTANT MANAGER – HEALTH AND WELLNESS (CONTRACT POSITION)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: IRC 989&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; The successful candidate will be expected to; (i) To coordinate the planning, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of multi-level campus-wide health education &amp; promotion programs. (ii) To develop health promotion &amp; education operational guidelines and their implementation plan.(iii) To identify strategic partnerships and grants opportunities to improve health promotion &amp; education services at the University of Botswana (iv) To participate in the development and distribution of health related IEC material targeted at different  groups within the University community (v) Provision of quality biometric screening for selected non-communicable diseases and HIV testing for the University community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; (vi)Health promotion &amp; education program related data/information management. (vii) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supervise subordinates and monitor their progress through the performance management system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;and (viii) attend to any other duties as assigned by the supervisor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Candidates should have (i) a minimum of Bachelors Degree in Health Education or related field (Nursing, Public Health etc)  (ii) At least 2 years post qualification experience in the related field; (iii) A demonstrable experience in clinical work, HIV testing, non-communicable disease screening, health promotion and community health programs will be an added advantage. (iv) A relevant Master’s Degree will be an added advantage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Strong organizational, interpersonal, oral and written communication. Ability to work effectively with students, staff and family members, Ability to work independently to manage multiple priorities, Computer literacy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;  The University offers competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position. They should also quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CVs (including telephone, telefax and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, names and addresses of three referees,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;least three reference letters and send complete documentation to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Appointments and Administration (Support) University of Botswana, Private Bag UB 0022, Gaborone, Botswana Telephone: (267) 355 2048/2040; Fax (267) 397 4796&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;strong&gt; E-mail:  &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:ramahobok@ub.ac.bw"&gt;ramahobok@ub.ac.bw&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to&lt;strong&gt; (i) quote the Vacancy Number and position applied for and (ii) Submit their reference letters directly to the above address before the stipulated closing date.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to Block 108 office 205.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

