            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;DEPUTY VICE CHANCELLOR STUDENT AFFAIRS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH SERVICES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW"&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: IRC 923&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CLINIC ASSISTANT/ORDERLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicants will be expected to: (i) support health care providers at the clinic; (ii) triaging and guiding patients through the clinic various facilities and procedures; (iii) supervise cleaners and ensuring cleanliness and aseptic techniques are maintained in the various units of the clinic; (iv) sterilizing medical equipment and sanitizing designated areas; (v) assist nurses in pottering and transporting patients for referrals (vi) delivers specimens and collects laboratory results as instructed by the nurse in charge; (vii) be available and assist in times of emergencies in the clinic; (viii) prepare reports on services provided; (ix) and attend to any other duties as assigned by the supervisor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements&lt;span&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates should have: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; minimum of a Junior Certificate; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; at least two (2) years’ experience working in a clinic, hospital or health care setting with similar responsibilities. &lt;strong&gt;The following will be added advantages:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; a certificate in Health Care Auxiliary or equivalent; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; any related Diploma in Health Care; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; relevant and additional professional training in phlebotomy, plaster technology, emergency care and counselling; and &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; work in a tertiary institution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualities: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ability to work effectively in a health team, ability to work independently to manage multiple priorities, computer literacy, high degree of commitment to work adhering to stipulated health standards and ethics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: The University offers a competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: Letters of application are to address the stated qualifications in their application letters and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position. They should quote the vacancy number of the position applied for, provide current CVs (including telephone and e-mail), certified true copies of educational certificates and transcripts, names and three (3) reference letters to: &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;he Human Resources Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Appointments and Administration, Private Bag 0022, Gaborone-Botswana; Telephone: (267) 355-2040/5731.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to: (i) &lt;strong&gt;Quote the Vacancy number and position applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the above&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;address. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;applications with incomplete information shall not be acknowledged. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

